  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    A person in this role leads a group of developers in the task of the development of a security architecture. A security&#xD;
    architecture is a representation of the best practices of the security community. It often includes the selection of&#xD;
    preferred security patterns for system design (&lt;b>&lt;i>security design patterns&lt;/i>&lt;/b>), the documentation of technical&#xD;
    policy (&lt;b>&lt;i>policy design patterns&lt;/i>&lt;/b>) concerning security implementation &lt;b>&lt;i>(security implementation&#xD;
    patterns&lt;/i>&lt;/b>) and &lt;b>&lt;i>security architectural patterns&lt;/i>&lt;/b> reflecting the key technical decisions that&#xD;
    constrain the overall security implementation for the project.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:RoleDescription>
